---
description: Guidelines for refactoring existing code.
alwaysApply: false
---
- Always run tests before and after refactoring changes.
- Ensure the git staging area is empty before refactoring.
- Identify all parts of the system that will be touched before refactoring. Ensure there exists tests for these interfaces before refactoring.
- Strive for readability, composability and robustness.
- Follow best conventions.
